SIMPLE: ornamentation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ornamentation
<hw>Or`na*men*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act or art of ornamenting, or the state of being
ornamented.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which ornaments.</def> <rj><au>C.
Kingsley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The ornaments embellishing an object, collectively;
<as>as, each room of the palace had a strikingly different
<ex>ornamentation</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ornamenter</ent>⟦br⟧
